begin
reserve R for  domRing-like  commutative Ring;
reserve c for (Element of R);
theorem
Th12: (for a,b,c being (Element of R) holds ((((c <> ( 0. R ) & c divides a) & c divides b) & c divides ( a + b )) implies ( ( a / c ) + ( b / c ) ) = ( ( a + b ) / c )))
proof
let a being (Element of R);
let b being (Element of R);
let c being (Element of R);
assume A1: c <> ( 0. R );
set e = ( b / c );
set d = ( a / c );
assume that
A2: (c divides a & c divides b)
and
A3: c divides ( a + b );
(( d * c ) = a & ( e * c ) = b) by A1,A2,CKB14:def 1;
then ( a + b ) = ( ( d + e ) * c ) by VECTSP_1:def 3;
then ( ( a + b ) / c ) = ( ( d + e ) * ( c / c ) ) by A1,A3,CKB24:1
.= ( ( d + e ) * ( 1. R ) ) by A1,CKB22:1
.= ( d + e ) by VECTSP_1:def 4;
hence thesis;
end;
